{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"polite-dutiful-drake","description":"Silent-success detection (wall-clock timeout + verdict schema-shape + structured refusal-as-content) plus two proven output self-heal tweaks on rebar's already-strong structured.py ladder.\n\n## Why\nA class of failures never raises — a safety refusal returned AS the answer (pydantic-ai #5221), an empty/truncated result that looks complete (#5769, #3219), a silent hang (#4681) — so exception classification structurally can't see them; they need result validation. Separately, rebar's `structured.py` already implements almost the whole OSS self-heal ladder (native-where-available, tolerant parse, deterministic json-repair BEFORE reask, targeted error-fed reask, fast-fail on truncation/refusal, bounded `OUTPUT_RETRIES=2`) — it needs only two cheap, proven additions.\n\n## What\n- Runtime result-validation on every gate call: reuse the existing `check_stop_reason`; add a verdict **schema-shape** check (a parseable verdict object — NOT \"non-empty output\", since a clean review legitimately has zero findings); detect refusal-as-content via the structured `incomplete_details` / finish_reason signal (#5221), NOT a content regex (which false-fires on tickets/diffs that discuss safety). The story-3 per-call wall-clock timeout is the silent-hang backstop.\n- Output self-heal in `src/rebar/llm/structured.py`: (1) pass the target Pydantic model into `json_repair` via its `schema=` arg (schema-guided deterministic repair, before any LLM reask); (2) include a bounded snippet of the model's faulty prior output in the targeted reask (the LangChain `RetryWithErrorOutputParser` / Instructor pattern — lets the model diff its mistake).\n\n## Scope\n- Runtime checks + the two `structured.py` tweaks.\n- NOT in scope: a second-interpreter \"fixer\" LLM — `structured.py` explicitly rejects it as an anti-pattern; keep that stance.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Refusal-as-content (via structured signal) and empty/truncated-looks-complete are detected and routed, not returned as a PASS/BLOCK verdict.\n- [ ] A verdict schema-shape check replaces any \"non-empty output\" heuristic; a zero-finding clean review still passes.\n- [ ] `json_repair` is called with `schema=<model>`; the targeted reask includes the bounded faulty prior output.\n- [ ] No second-LLM fixer is introduced.\n- [ ] RED silent-success cases flip GREEN; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/structured.py`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`, the gate verdict-finalization path.","id":"978d-1d5d-8287-47bc","parent_id":"jira-reb-687","priority":2,"tags":["llm-resilience"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Silent-success detection + output self-heal (schema-guided repair, faulty-output reask)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783557856107459001,"uuid":"e7b13042-fae3-4f27-b027-cd84b28ba29a"}